<item>
            <title>[LU-105] Add -D logdir option to Auster so that the whole logdir can be passed - enables parent process to share log directory with Auster</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-105</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When capturing console logs etc. The whole system must know where the logs will be stored. At present this decision is made locally to auster. By adding a -D option which is the whole log directory path - not just the toplevel - multiple processes can use the same log directory.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
